<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3241] No syntax error when compiling statement with unterminated comment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3241</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Compiling a statement with an unterminated comment doesn&apos;t raise a syntax error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij&amp;gt; prepare p as &apos;values 1 /* unterminated comment &apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; execute p;&lt;br/&gt;
1          &lt;br/&gt;
-----------&lt;br/&gt;
1          &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1 row selected&lt;/p&gt;</description>
